ir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Please check the course LUNA pages for today's schedule and topics.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>", ""], "第14回": ["<div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">【Classes and Examinations Period</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>】(Week 1)</div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">\"Face-to-face class\" / 《360 minutes》</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Please check the course LUNA pages for today's schedule and topics.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>", ""], "第15回": ["<div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">【Flex Hours</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>】</div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">\"Online class (Format will be announced in each class)\"/ 《360 minutes》</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div><div style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Please check the course LUNA pages for the schedule and topics for flex hours.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>", ""], "授業計画1": "<p class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;font-size-adjust:none;font-language-override:normal;font-kerning:auto;font-optical-sizing:auto;font-feature-settings:normal;font-variation-settings:normal;font-variant-position:normal;font-variant-emoji:normal;font-stretch:normal;font-size:13.3px;line-height:normal;-webkit-text-stroke-color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"font-kerning:none;\">&lt;Lecture&gt; Each topic will be introduced on a four-week cycle following a problem - solution genre. The first week, will introduce an SDG, providing background information and important definitions. The second week will address the causes of the problem and the interrelatedness of the topic with other SDGs. The third and fourth weeks will introduce solutions to the problem and discuss the successes and limitations.&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;font-size-adjust:none;font-language-override:normal;font-kerning:auto;font-optical-sizing:auto;font-feature-settings:normal;font-variation-settings:normal;font-variant-position:normal;font-variant-emoji:normal;font-stretch:normal;font-size:13.3px;line-height:normal;-webkit-text-stroke-color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"font-kerning:none;\">&lt;Lecture Bridge Reading and Discussion&gt; Materials and topics will follow the lecture course while also introducing discussion skills and improving vocabulary knowledge.&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;font-size-adjust:none;font-language-override:normal;font-kerning:auto;font-optical-sizing:auto;font-feature-settings:normal;font-variation-settings:normal;font-variant-position:normal;font-variant-emoji:normal;font-stretch:normal;font-size:13.3px;line-height:normal;-webkit-text-stroke-color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"font-kerning:none;\">&lt;Lecture Bridge Reading and Writing&gt;&nbsp;</span><span class=\"s2\" style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;font-variant-position:normal;font-variant-emoji:normal;font-size-adjust:none;font-language-override:normal;font-optical-sizing:auto;font-feature-settings:normal;font-variation-settings:normal;font-stretch:normal;line-height:normal;font-kerning:none;\">&nbsp;The majority of the course will be spent researching, analyzing sources and paragraphs, and writing academic essays.</span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;font-size-adjust:none;font-language-override:normal;font-kerning:auto;font-optical-sizing:auto;font-feature-settings:normal;font-variation-settings:normal;font-variant-position:normal;font-variant-emoji:normal;font-stretch:normal;font-size:13.3px;line-height:normal;-webkit-text-stroke-color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"font-kerning:none;\">&lt;Special Topics&gt; The schedule for each Special Topics course will depend on the teacher and will be announced to students at the beginning of the class.</span></p>", "授業外学習2": "<p class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;font-size-adjust:none;font-language-override:normal;font-kerning:auto;font-optical-sizing:auto;font-feature-settings:normal;font-variation-settings:normal;font-variant-position:normal;font-variant-emoji:normal;font-stretch:normal;font-size:13.3px;line-height:normal;-webkit-text-stroke-color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"font-kerning:none;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Lecture&gt; Students will read and complete preparation worksheets for each lecture. Students will need to review materials throughout the semester.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></p><p class=\"p2\" style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;font-size-adjust:none;font-language-override:normal;font-kerning:auto;font-optical-sizing:auto;font-feature-settings:normal;font-variation-settings:normal;font-variant-position:normal;font-variant-emoji:normal;font-stretch:normal;font-size:13.3px;line-height:normal;-webkit-text-stroke-color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><span class=\"s2\" style=\"font-kerning:none;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Lecture Bridge Reading and Discussion&gt; To prepare for the discussions, students will read articles, attend the lectures, and research the topic on the Internet In the discussions, they present, discuss, and explore the topics based on the lecture, reading, and research.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></p><p class=\"p2\" style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;font-size-adjust:none;font-language-override:normal;font-kerning:auto;font-optical-sizing:auto;font-feature-settings:normal;font-variation-settings:normal;font-variant-position:normal;font-variant-emoji:normal;font-stretch:normal;font-size:13.3px;line-height:normal;-webkit-text-stroke-color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><span class=\"s2\" style=\"font-kerning:none;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Lecture Bridge Reading and Writing&gt; Students will research sources and write academic essays as well as preparation for the quiz.</span></span></span></span></span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;font-size-adjust:none;font-language-override:normal;font-kerning:auto;font-optical-sizing:auto;font-feature-settings:normal;font-variation-settings:normal;font-variant-position:normal;font-variant-emoji:normal;font-stretch:normal;font-size:13.3px;line-height:normal;-webkit-text-stroke-color:rgb(0,0,0);\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"font-kerning:none;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Special Topics&gt; Each Special Topics course will have different homework associated with the topic.</span></span></span></span></span></p>"}, "評価": {"教科書/Required texts0": ["Materials will be available on LUNA. You should bring your materials to class on your device (computer / tablet).&nbsp;Some special topics courses may require other materials. Your teacher will let you know on the first day of class if you need to purchase anything extra."], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students0": ["Conducted in class"], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students1": ["Each class subject is arranged on the curriculum based on the Diploma Policy (DP) and Curriculum Policy (CP) established by each faculty and graduate school.By studying this course with DP/CP in mind, you will develop the abilities expected by each faculty and graduate school.The DP, CP, and curriculum table (list of classes, etc.) for each faculty/graduate school are posted in the link below, so please use them as a reference for your study plan.https://kwic .kwansei.ac.jp/cabinet/reference?typeCd=0&amp;cabinetId=557&amp;directLink=1*Link to kwic (only current students can view)"], "成績評価Grading0": ["種別　Type備考　Note", "割合　Percentage", "評価基準等　Grading Criteria etc."], "成績評価Grading1": ["その他／Others (99)", "100 %", "See the Evaluation Note below"], "成績評価Grading2": ["備考　Note &lt;Lecture&gt; Students will be assessed on three tests: unit 1 test, unit 2 test, and a final exam. There are also pop quizzes. This means they are not announced before the class. If a student is absent, they cannot be made up. Instead, each student's lowest grade will be dropped so a student can a quiz without it affecting their score. There is also one homework submission.&nbsp;&lt;Lecture Bridge Reading and Discussion&gt; Grades are based on performance in 3-4 person discussions, including expression of required spoken contents in English and interactive response skills. In addition, presentation and minor speaking tasks are required.&nbsp;&lt;Lecture Bridge Reading and Writing&gt; Evaluation is based on folio writing, outlining, draft writing, and completing a quiz.&lt;Special Topics&gt; Each Special Topics Course is graded differently. Your teacher will provide you with the course syllabus on the first day of class."], "更新日時/Date of Update0": ["2026年02月19日 16時39分29秒"], "項番No.0": [], "項番No.1": ["2026年度", "秋学期／Fall", "火曜２時限／Tuesday 2", "秋学期／Fall", "教室未定"], "項番No.2": ["2026年度", "秋学期／Fall", "水曜１時限／Wednesday 1", "秋学期／Fall", "教室未定"], "項番No.3": ["2026年度", "秋学期／Fall", "木曜３時限／Thursday 3", "秋学期／Fall", "教室未定"]}, "campas": 1, "name": "【200】英語コミュニケーションVI　Ａ／English Communication 6", "管理部署": 7, "単位数": 4, "担当者": "ジョーダン　Ｊ．（JORDAN JENNIFER ALINE） ", "履修基準年度": "１年", "履修登録方法": "予備登録", "開講期": 2, "時限1": 8, "時限2": 14, "時限3": 23, "評価1": 6, "成績評価備考": "備考　Note\n<Lecture> Students will be assessed on three tests: unit 1 test, unit 2 test, and a final exam. There are also pop quizzes. This means they are not announced before the class. If a student is absent, they cannot be made up. Instead, each student's lowest grade will be dropped so a student can a quiz without it affecting their score. There is also one homework submission. \n<Lecture Bridge Reading and Discussion> Grades are based on performance in 3-4 person discussions, including expression of required spoken contents in English and interactive response skills. In addition, presentation and minor speaking tasks are required. \n<Lecture Bridge Reading and Writing> Evaluation is based on folio writing, outlining, draft writing, and completing a quiz.\n<Special Topics> Each Special Topics Course is graded differently. Your teacher will provide you with the course syllabus on the first day of class."}